# {{Adapter Display Name}} Integration

This page documents the `contextweaver.adapters.{{adapter_name}}` adapter.

## Install

```bash
pip install 'contextweaver[{{extra_name}}]'
```

If the provider SDK is already installed by your application, the adapter conversion functions can also be used directly from a core contextweaver install as long as you pass provider-like objects and do not call provider-specific helpers.

## Convert tools

```python
from contextweaver.adapters.{{adapter_name}} import from_{{adapter_name}}_tools

selectable_items = from_{{adapter_name}}_tools(provider_tools, namespace="{{adapter_name}}")
```

The returned objects are contextweaver `SelectableItem`s and can be registered in a catalog or routed like any other tools.

## Convert history

```python
from contextweaver.adapters.{{adapter_name}} import from_{{adapter_name}}_history

context_items = from_{{adapter_name}}_history(provider_messages)
```

Delete this section if the provider does not expose a message/history shape.

## Boundaries

- The adapter converts provider objects; it does not execute provider tools.
- Tests use local fakes and do not call live APIs.
- Provider SDK imports are optional and guarded.
- Provider-specific objects should not leak beyond the adapter boundary.

## Troubleshooting

If you see an import error for `{{provider_package}}`, install the optional extra shown above or install the provider SDK in your application environment.